  "prompt": "My username is no longer available on Skype. Why?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your Skype username is no longer available. Here are some possible explanations:\n\n1. **Account Deactivation or Deletion**: If you haven't used your Skype account for a long time, Microsoft (which owns Skype) might have deactivated or deleted it due to inactivity. This could result in your username becoming available for others to claim.\n\n2. **Change in Policy or System**: Skype has transitioned to using Microsoft accounts, and there might have been changes in how usernames are handled. If your username was tied to an older Skype ID, it might no longer be recognized.\n\n3. **Username Reclaimed**: Microsoft periodically reviews and reclaims inactive usernames. If your account was deemed inactive, your username might have been released for others to use.\n\n4. **Account Compromise or Hack**: If your account was compromised, the hacker might have changed the username or settings, making it unavailable to you.\n\n5. **Technical Glitch**: There could be a temporary technical issue with Skype or your account, causing the username to appear unavailable.\n\n### What to Do:\n- **Check Your Account Status**: Log in to your Microsoft account (if you\u2019ve linked Skype to it) and verify your Skype account status.\n- **Recover Your Account**: If your account was deactivated, follow the account recovery process provided by Skype/Microsoft.\n- **Contact Skype Support**: Reach out to Skype customer support for assistance. They can investigate why your username is unavailable and help you regain access.\n- **Choose a New Username**: If your old username is no longer available, you might need to select a new one.\n\nLet me know if you'd like detailed steps for any of these actions!",
